{"title_page": "Donovan Peoples-Jones", "text_new": "{{short description|American football wide receiver and return specialist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Donovan Peoples-Jones\n| image               = Donavan Peoples-Jones (37055143700).jpg\n| caption             = \n| number              = \n| current_team        = Cleveland Browns\n| position            = [[Wide receiver]]<br>[[Return specialist]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1999|2|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Detroit]], Michigan\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 2\n| weight_lb           = 199\n| high_school         = [[Cass Technical High School|Detroit (MI) Cass Tech]]\n| college             = [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]]\n| draftyear           = 2020\n| draftround          = 6\n| draftpick           = 187\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Cleveland Browns]]  ({{NFL Year|2020}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Unsigned draft pick\n| highlights          = \n* 2\u00d7 All-[[Big Ten Conference|Big Ten]] Third-team ([[2018 All-Big Ten Conference football team|2018]], [[2019 All-Big Ten Conference football team|2019]])\n* Freshman All-American (2017)\n* Team Rookie of the Year Award (2017)\n*''USA Today'' High School All-American ([[2016 USA Today All-USA high school football team|2016]])\n| statleague          = \n| statseason          = \n| statweek            = \n| statlabel1          = \n| statvalue1          = \n| statlabel2          = \n| statvalue2          = \n| statlabel3          = \n| statvalue3          = \n| nfl                 = \n}}\n'''Donovan Peoples-Jones''' (born February 19, 1999), also known as \"'''DPJ'''\",<ref>{{cite news|title=Harbaugh raves about Michigan freshman receivers|author=Angelique S. Chengelis|newspaper=The Detroit News|date=August 11, 2017|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/2017/08/11/um-coach-harbaugh-says-kids-alright/104515754/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones, Tarik Black flash skills in Michigan's spring game|author=Mark Snyder|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=April 16, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/04/16/michigan-football-freshman-receivers/100549010/}}</ref> is an [[American football]] [[wide receiver]] and [[return specialist]] for the [[Cleveland Browns]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played college football for the [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan Wolverines]].\n\n==Early life==\nDonovan Peoples-Jones was born in Detroit on February 19, 1999 to Roslyn Peoples and Eddie Jones. He attended [[Cass Technical High School]] where he was a five-star recruit and rated as the best wide receiver recruit from the state of Michigan since [[Charles Rogers (American football)|Charles Rogers]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=Donovan People-Jones|publisher=University of Michigan|accessdate=September 2, 2017|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=16358}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones is state's best WR recruit since 2000|newspaper=[[Mlive.com]]|date=December 15, 2016|url=http://highschoolsports.mlive.com/news/article/-8482570732985264379/with-commitment-coming-donovan-peoples-jones-is-states-best-wr-recruit-since-2000/}}</ref> On December 15, 2016, he committed to play for the [[University of Michigan]] in a nationally televised press conference on [[ESPN2]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cass Tech WR Donovan Peoples-Jones commits to Michigan football|author=Chris Nelsen|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=December 15, 2016|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/high-school/2016/12/15/donovan-peoples-jones-michigan-football/95490468/}}</ref>{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=yes|collapse=no|year=2017}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry|40=4.45|recruit=Donovan Peoples-Jones|position=[[Wide Receiver|WR]]|hometown=Detroit, Michigan|highschool=[[Cass Technical High School]]|feet=6|inches=2|weight=193|commitdate=December 15, 2016|scout stars=5|rivals stars=5|247 stars=5|espn stars=4}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit End|40=yes|year=2017|rivals ref title=Michigan Football Commitments|espn ref title=ESPN|rivals school=Michigan|espn schoolid=130|rivals overall=12|247 overall=26|espn overall=22|accessdate=May 23, 2018|bball=|247Sports ref title=Donovan Peoples-Jones}}\n\n\n==College career==\nAfter committing to Michigan, Peoples-Jones enrolled early in January 2017. After watching Peoples-Jones and fellow freshman [[Tarik Black (American football)|Tarik Black]] in spring practice, offensive lineman [[Mason Cole]] predicted the pair were \"going to be unbelievable.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=UM's Black, Peoples-Jones 'are going to be unbelievable'|author=Angelique S. Chengelis|newspaper=The Detroit News|date=August 30, 2017|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/08/30/ums-black-peoples-jones-going-unbelievable/105136124/}}</ref>\n\nOn September 2, 2017, Peoples-Jones started at punt returner as a true freshman in Michigan's season opener against [[2017 Florida Gators football team|Florida]]. He returned five punts for 40 yards, including an 18-yard return.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones trusting plan, focused on improvement|author=Nick Baumgardner|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=September 5, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/09/05/michigan-wolverines-football-donovan-peoples-jones/635803001/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=For Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones, Step 1 is returning kicks|newspaper=[[Mlive.com]]|date=September 6, 2016|author=Aaron McMann|url=http://www.mlive.com/wolverines/index.ssf/2017/09/for_michigans_donovan_peoples-.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones embraces fearless attitude at punt returner|newspaper=[[The Michigan Daily]]|date=September 5, 2017|author=Orion Sang|url=https://www.michigandaily.com/section/football/michigan-football-donovan-peoples-jones-punt-returner-wilton-speight}}</ref> In his second game, he ran 44 yards on a jet sweep in the first quarter against [[2017 Cincinnati Bearcats football team|Cincinnati]]. In his third game, he returned two punts for 104 yards, including a 79-yard return for a touchdown in the third quarter against [[2017 Air Force Falcons football team|Air Force]]. His 79-yard return for a touchdown was the longest by any Michigan punt returner since [[Steve Breaston]] went 83 yards against Indiana in 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones earns props from friends, foes for TD|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=September 16, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/09/16/donovan-peoples-jones-punt-return-michigan-wolverines/674077001/}}</ref> He finished with the second-most return attempts and eighth-most return yards in a single season by a Wolverine, and also caught 22 passes for 277 yards. Following an outstanding freshman season, he was named a Freshman All-American by [[Football Writers Association of America]] and 247 Sports, and was named Michigan's Rookie of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones Named FWAA Freshman All-American|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=January 8, 2018|date=January 8, 2018|url=http://mgoblue.com/news/2017/12/6/football-michigan-2017-all-america-honors.aspx}}</ref> \n\nDuring the 2018 season, Peoples-Jones led the team with 39 receptions, for 541 yards and seven touchdowns. Peoples-Jones ranked second in the Big Ten in punt return average (10.1) among players with 10 returns or more, and his 64 career return attempts ranks fourth in Michigan program history. On October 20, 2018 in a rivalry game against Michigan State, Peoples-Jones had a career long reception of 79 yards for a touchdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mgoblue.com/sports/football/roster/donovan-peoples-jones/19060|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones \u2013 Football|website=University of Michigan Athletics|language=en|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> Following the season, he was named to the All-Big Ten special teams third-team, by both the coaches and media, and the All-Big Ten offensive teams third-team by coaches.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fourteen Wolverines Earn All-Big Ten Honors on Defense, Special Teams|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=November 27, 2018|date=November 27, 2017|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2018/11/27/football-fourteen-wolverines-earn-all-big-ten-honors-on-defense-special-teams.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Eleven Michigan Players Selected for All-Big Ten Honors on Offense|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=November 27, 2018|date=November 27, 2017|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2018/11/28/football-eleven-michigan-players-selected-for-all-big-ten-honors-on-offense.aspx}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the 2019 season, he was named to the All-Big Ten special teams third-team by the media, and the All-Big Ten offensive team honorable mention by the media.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fourteen Wolverines Honored by Big Ten on Defense and Special Teams|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=December 3, 2019|date=December 3, 2019|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2019/12/3/football-fourteen-wolverines-honored-by-big-ten-on-defense-and-special-teams.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Thirteen Michigan Players Honored by Big Ten on Offense|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=December 4, 2019|date=December 4, 2019|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2019/12/4/football-thirteen-michigan-players-honored-by-big-ten-on-offense.aspx}}</ref> On January 4, 2020, Peoples-Jones announced he would forego his final season of eligibility to enter the 2020 NFL draft.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college/michigan/football/michigan-wolverines-football-donovan-peoples-jones-decalring-for-nfl-draft-nico-collins-cesar-ruiz-jim-harbaugh|title=BREAKING: Donovan Peoples-Jones Declares For NFL Draft|website=Maven|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2020/01/04/donovan-peoples-jones-nfl-draft-michigan-football/2814544001/|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones declares for 2020 NFL draft|last=Sang|first=Orion|website=Detroit Free Press|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref>\n\n=== College statistics ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Team\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Conf\n! rowspan=\"2\" |{{tooltip|G|Games}}\n! colspan=\"4\" |Receiving\n! colspan=\"4\" |Rushing\n! colspan=\"4\" |Returns\n|-\n!Rec\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n!Att\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n!Ret\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n|-\n|[[2017 Michigan Wolverines football team|2017]]\n|[[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]]\n|[[Big Ten Conference|Big Ten]]\n|13\n|22\n|277\n|12.6\n|0\n|4\n|57\n|14.3\n|0\n|40\n|320\n|8.0\n|1\n|-\n|[[2018 Michigan Wolverines football team|2018]]\n|Michigan\n|Big Ten\n|13\n|47\n|612\n|13.0\n|8\n|3\n|37\n|12.3\n|0\n|25\n|250\n|10.0\n|1\n|-\n|[[2019 Michigan Wolverines football team|2019]]\n|Michigan\n|Big Ten\n|11\n|34\n|438\n|12.9\n|6\n|2\n| \u22127\n| \u22123.5\n|0\n|24\n|173\n|7.2\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career\n!37\n!103\n!1,327\n!12.9\n!14\n!9\n!87\n!9.7\n!0\n!89\n!743\n!8.3\n!2\n|-\n| colspan=\"16\" |All values from [[Sports Reference]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/donovan-peoples-jones-1.html|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones College Stats|last=|first=|date=|website=College Football at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mgoblue.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=16358 Michigan Wolverines bio]\n\n{{Cleveland Browns roster navbox}}\n{{Browns2020DraftPicks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:People-Jones, Donovan}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football wide receivers]]\n[[Category:Michigan Wolverines football players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Detroit]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Michigan]]\n[[Category:Cleveland Browns players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football wide receiver and return specialist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Donovan Peoples-Jones\n| image               = Donavan Peoples-Jones (37055143700).jpg\n| caption             = \n| number              = \n| current_team        = Cleveland Browns\n| position            = [[Wide receiver]], [[return specialist]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1999|2|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Detroit]], Michigan\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 2\n| weight_lb           = 199\n| high_school         = [[Cass Technical High School|Detroit (MI) Cass Tech]]\n| college             = [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]]\n| draftyear           = 2020\n| draftround          = 6\n| draftpick           = 187\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Cleveland Browns]]  ({{NFL Year|2020}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Unsigned draft pick\n| highlights          = \n* 2\u00d7 All-[[Big Ten Conference|Big Ten]] Third-team ([[2018 All-Big Ten Conference football team|2018]], [[2019 All-Big Ten Conference football team|2019]])\n* Freshman All-American (2017)\n* Team Rookie of the Year Award (2017)\n*''USA Today'' High School All-American ([[2016 USA Today All-USA high school football team|2016]])\n| statleague          = \n| statseason          = \n| statweek            = \n| statlabel1          = \n| statvalue1          = \n| statlabel2          = \n| statvalue2          = \n| statlabel3          = \n| statvalue3          = \n| nfl                 = \n}}\n'''Donovan Peoples-Jones''' (born February 19, 1999), also known as \"'''DPJ'''\",<ref>{{cite news|title=Harbaugh raves about Michigan freshman receivers|author=Angelique S. Chengelis|newspaper=The Detroit News|date=August 11, 2017|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/2017/08/11/um-coach-harbaugh-says-kids-alright/104515754/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones, Tarik Black flash skills in Michigan's spring game|author=Mark Snyder|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=April 16, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/04/16/michigan-football-freshman-receivers/100549010/}}</ref> is an [[American football]] [[wide receiver]] and [[return specialist]] for the [[Cleveland Browns]]. He played college football for the [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan Wolverines]].\n\n==Early life==\nDonovan Peoples-Jones was born in Detroit on February 19, 1999 to Roslyn Peoples and Eddie Jones. He attended [[Cass Technical High School]] where he was a five-star recruit and rated as the best wide receiver recruit from the state of Michigan since [[Charles Rogers (American football)|Charles Rogers]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=Donovan People-Jones|publisher=University of Michigan|accessdate=September 2, 2017|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=16358}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones is state's best WR recruit since 2000|newspaper=[[Mlive.com]]|date=December 15, 2016|url=http://highschoolsports.mlive.com/news/article/-8482570732985264379/with-commitment-coming-donovan-peoples-jones-is-states-best-wr-recruit-since-2000/}}</ref> On December 15, 2016, he committed to play for the [[University of Michigan]] in a nationally televised press conference on [[ESPN2]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cass Tech WR Donovan Peoples-Jones commits to Michigan football|author=Chris Nelsen|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=December 15, 2016|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/high-school/2016/12/15/donovan-peoples-jones-michigan-football/95490468/}}</ref>{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=yes|collapse=no|year=2017}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry|40=4.45|recruit=Donovan Peoples-Jones|position=[[Wide Receiver|WR]]|hometown=Detroit, Michigan|highschool=[[Cass Technical High School]]|feet=6|inches=2|weight=193|commitdate=December 15, 2016|scout stars=5|rivals stars=5|247 stars=5|espn stars=4}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit End|40=yes|year=2017|rivals ref title=Michigan Football Commitments|espn ref title=ESPN|rivals school=Michigan|espn schoolid=130|rivals overall=12|247 overall=26|espn overall=22|accessdate=May 23, 2018|bball=|247Sports ref title=Donovan Peoples-Jones}}\n\n\n==College career==\nAfter committing to Michigan, Peoples-Jones enrolled early in January 2017. After watching Peoples-Jones and fellow freshman [[Tarik Black (American football)|Tarik Black]] in spring practice, offensive lineman [[Mason Cole]] predicted the pair were \"going to be unbelievable.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=UM's Black, Peoples-Jones 'are going to be unbelievable'|author=Angelique S. Chengelis|newspaper=The Detroit News|date=August 30, 2017|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/08/30/ums-black-peoples-jones-going-unbelievable/105136124/}}</ref>\n\nOn September 2, 2017, Peoples-Jones started at punt returner as a true freshman in Michigan's season opener against [[2017 Florida Gators football team|Florida]]. He returned five punts for 40 yards, including an 18-yard return.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones trusting plan, focused on improvement|author=Nick Baumgardner|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=September 5, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/09/05/michigan-wolverines-football-donovan-peoples-jones/635803001/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=For Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones, Step 1 is returning kicks|newspaper=[[Mlive.com]]|date=September 6, 2016|author=Aaron McMann|url=http://www.mlive.com/wolverines/index.ssf/2017/09/for_michigans_donovan_peoples-.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones embraces fearless attitude at punt returner|newspaper=[[The Michigan Daily]]|date=September 5, 2017|author=Orion Sang|url=https://www.michigandaily.com/section/football/michigan-football-donovan-peoples-jones-punt-returner-wilton-speight}}</ref> In his second game, he ran 44 yards on a jet sweep in the first quarter against [[2017 Cincinnati Bearcats football team|Cincinnati]]. In his third game, he returned two punts for 104 yards, including a 79-yard return for a touchdown in the third quarter against [[2017 Air Force Falcons football team|Air Force]]. His 79-yard return for a touchdown was the longest by any Michigan punt returner since [[Steve Breaston]] went 83 yards against Indiana in 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones earns props from friends, foes for TD|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|date=September 16, 2017|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2017/09/16/donovan-peoples-jones-punt-return-michigan-wolverines/674077001/}}</ref> He finished with the second-most return attempts and eighth-most return yards in a single season by a Wolverine, and also caught 22 passes for 277 yards. Following an outstanding freshman season, he was named a Freshman All-American by [[Football Writers Association of America]] and 247 Sports, and was named Michigan's Rookie of the Year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Peoples-Jones Named FWAA Freshman All-American|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=January 8, 2018|date=January 8, 2018|url=http://mgoblue.com/news/2017/12/6/football-michigan-2017-all-america-honors.aspx}}</ref> \n\nDuring the 2018 season, Peoples-Jones led the team with 39 receptions, for 541 yards and seven touchdowns. Peoples-Jones ranked second in the Big Ten in punt return average (10.1) among players with 10 returns or more, and his 64 career return attempts ranks fourth in Michigan program history. On October 20, 2018 in a rivalry game against Michigan State, Peoples-Jones had a career long reception of 79 yards for a touchdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mgoblue.com/sports/football/roster/donovan-peoples-jones/19060|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones \u2013 Football|website=University of Michigan Athletics|language=en|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> Following the season, he was named to the All-Big Ten special teams third-team, by both the coaches and media, and the All-Big Ten offensive teams third-team by coaches.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fourteen Wolverines Earn All-Big Ten Honors on Defense, Special Teams|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=November 27, 2018|date=November 27, 2017|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2018/11/27/football-fourteen-wolverines-earn-all-big-ten-honors-on-defense-special-teams.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Eleven Michigan Players Selected for All-Big Ten Honors on Offense|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=November 27, 2018|date=November 27, 2017|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2018/11/28/football-eleven-michigan-players-selected-for-all-big-ten-honors-on-offense.aspx}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the 2019 season, he was named to the All-Big Ten special teams third-team by the media, and the All-Big Ten offensive team honorable mention by the media.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fourteen Wolverines Honored by Big Ten on Defense and Special Teams|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=December 3, 2019|date=December 3, 2019|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2019/12/3/football-fourteen-wolverines-honored-by-big-ten-on-defense-and-special-teams.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Thirteen Michigan Players Honored by Big Ten on Offense|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=December 4, 2019|date=December 4, 2019|url=https://mgoblue.com/news/2019/12/4/football-thirteen-michigan-players-honored-by-big-ten-on-offense.aspx}}</ref> On January 4, 2020, Peoples-Jones announced he would forego his final season of eligibility to enter the 2020 NFL draft.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college/michigan/football/michigan-wolverines-football-donovan-peoples-jones-decalring-for-nfl-draft-nico-collins-cesar-ruiz-jim-harbaugh|title=BREAKING: Donovan Peoples-Jones Declares For NFL Draft|website=Maven|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/college/university-michigan/wolverines/2020/01/04/donovan-peoples-jones-nfl-draft-michigan-football/2814544001/|title=Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones declares for 2020 NFL draft|last=Sang|first=Orion|website=Detroit Free Press|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref>\n\n=== College statistics ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Team\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Conf\n! rowspan=\"2\" |{{tooltip|G|Games}}\n! colspan=\"4\" |Receiving\n! colspan=\"4\" |Rushing\n! colspan=\"4\" |Returns\n|-\n!Rec\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n!Att\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n!Ret\n!Yds\n!Avg\n!TD\n|-\n|[[2017 Michigan Wolverines football team|2017]]\n|[[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]]\n|[[Big Ten Conference|Big Ten]]\n|13\n|22\n|277\n|12.6\n|0\n|4\n|57\n|14.3\n|0\n|40\n|320\n|8.0\n|1\n|-\n|[[2018 Michigan Wolverines football team|2018]]\n|Michigan\n|Big Ten\n|13\n|47\n|612\n|13.0\n|8\n|3\n|37\n|12.3\n|0\n|25\n|250\n|10.0\n|1\n|-\n|[[2019 Michigan Wolverines football team|2019]]\n|Michigan\n|Big Ten\n|11\n|34\n|438\n|12.9\n|6\n|2\n| \u22127\n| \u22123.5\n|0\n|24\n|173\n|7.2\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career\n!37\n!103\n!1,327\n!12.9\n!14\n!9\n!87\n!9.7\n!0\n!89\n!743\n!8.3\n!2\n|-\n| colspan=\"16\" |All values from [[Sports Reference]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/donovan-peoples-jones-1.html|title=Donovan Peoples-Jones College Stats|last=|first=|date=|website=College Football at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* 